    <fr:p>Since the question is local, we can assume that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is affine and that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {L}=\mathcal {O}_X]]></fr:tex>.
      This then reduces to a problem of commutative algebra, and, more specifically, of local algebra:
      if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is a regular locality, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-module whose support is of dimension <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\leqslant  q=n-p]]></fr:tex>, then we have to prove that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Ext}_A^i(M,A)=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i<p]]></fr:tex> and that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Ext}_A^p(M,A)=\operatorname {Hom}_A(M,\operatorname {Ext}^p(A/\mathfrak {J},A))]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {J}]]></fr:tex> is an arbitrary ideal of "dimension" <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\leqslant  q]]></fr:tex> that annihilates <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>.
      For the first claim, we proceed by induction on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex>:
      an immediate <fr:em>dévissage</fr:em> leads to the case where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is of the form <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A/\mathfrak {J}]]></fr:tex>, and thus leads, by replacing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {J}]]></fr:tex> with a smaller ideal and using the induction hypothesis, as well as the exact sequence of the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Ext}]]></fr:tex>, to the case where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {J}]]></fr:tex> is generated by a "system of parameters", as in <fr:ref
addr="fga1-proposition-4"
href="fga1-proposition-4.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="4" />, where the result is immediate.
      The previous result implies that, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {J}]]></fr:tex> is a fixed ideal of "dimension" <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\leqslant  q]]></fr:tex>, then the contravariant functor <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E(M)=\operatorname {Ext}_A^p(M,A)]]></fr:tex> to the category of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(A/\mathfrak {J})]]></fr:tex>-modules is left exact;
      furthermore, it sends direct sums to direct products, from which it easily follows that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E(M)=\operatorname {Hom}_A(M,E(A))]]></fr:tex>.
      Finally, the last claim of <fr:ref
addr="fga1-proposition-5"
href="fga1-proposition-5.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="5" /> is more subtle, and follows from an intrinsic characterisation of the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E^i(F)]]></fr:tex> via a local duality theorem which cannot be stated here.</fr:p>
