display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
    Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {F}]]></fr:tex> be a coherent algebraic sheaf on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> with support contained in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {L}]]></fr:tex> be a locally-free algebraic sheaf on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
    Then the sheaves <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {E}\kern  -1.5pt\mathit {xt}_{\mathcal {O}_X}^i(\mathscr {F},\mathscr {L})]]></fr:tex> are zero for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i<p]]></fr:tex>, and, when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i=p]]></fr:tex>, there is a canonical isomorphism

