    where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {J}]]></fr:tex> denotes an arbitrary sheaf of ideals on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> that annihilates <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {F}]]></fr:tex> and has <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> as its set of zeros.
    In particular, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {F}]]></fr:tex> is a coherent algebraic sheaf on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, then

