    Finally, with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {F}]]></fr:tex> still a coherent algebraic sheaf on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, the sheaves <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {E}^i=\mathscr {E}\kern  -1.5pt\mathit {xt}_{\mathcal {O}_X}^{p+i}(\mathscr {F},\Omega _X^n)]]></fr:tex> do not depend on the choice of immersion of the algebraic space <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> into the non-singular algebraic variety <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  
    
